<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880311-0031 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Environmental Power Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> POWR BLTA </CO><IN> UTI </IN><TEXT>   Environmental Power Corp., Boston, said it signed contracts with Blount Inc. of Montgomery, Ala., valued at $170 million under which Blount will build, operate and maintain coal-fired electric generation plants for Environmental Power.    Under one of the contracts, valued at about $65 million, Blount, a construction and manufacturing concern, will design and build a 45,000-kilowatt plant in Sunnyside, Utah, which is scheduled for completion in 1990.    Under another contract, valued at about $105 million, Blount will design and build an 80,000-kilowatt plant in Scrubgrass, Pa., which also is scheduled for completion in 1990, Environmental Power added.    Environmental Power, which acquires and operates electrical generating plants, said the contracts with Blount &quot;are major cornerstone contracts for our two largest projects to date.&quot; </TEXT></DOC>